   <prefercite>
            <head>Cite As:</head>
            <p> #53-2-2391. Division of Rare and Manuscript Collections, Cornell University Library.</p>
            <p>Field notes follow the standard for North American Ichthyology summarized on pp. 13-16 in Fishes of the Great Lakes Region (1947), by C. Hubbs and K. Lagler. The numbering convention is initials, number of collection, year (e.g. ECR-10-1935 is the tenth collection made in 1935 by Edward C. Raney). Beginning in 1936, he numbered the notes sequentially, e.g. ECR-254.</p>
